				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				In response to fungi flamers:<BR>
<BR>
Not all &quot;fungi-flamers&quot; or &quot;anti-fungi&quot; people are just angry, upset, or jealous. Given, plenty of them are, and more likely most of them, but i don't think its fair either for us to make fun of them because they aren't as economically-successful as us in Everquest. <BR>
<BR>
(thats the end of being nice)<BR>
<BR>
but does it really matter what they say about fungi tunic? i mean.. its not like they are going to buy it off you, or even get one till 50 anyway..<BR>
<BR>
In response to effectiveness of fungi twinks:<BR>
<BR>
Anyone who has owned, owns, or is buying a fungi tunic understands the benifit of it. At higher levels, mainly 45 plus, it is for warriors, rogues, monks, and tanks that can't heal themselves. It becomes a down time tool... thats about it. For all pre 45 twinks, it is godly. And for shamans, there is no denying the superior power of fungi tunic w/ regen spells and canabalizing. You are practically never out of mana. <BR>
<BR>
In response to Price of Fungi:<BR>
<BR>
Fugni is expensive. end of story. buy it or camp it...those are your options<BR>
<BR>
But take from these rumors, speculations, theories, and all around B.M. that you will, all i know is i've gotten my warrior to 27 with only 1 day (game play) of hunting<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
o yeah... fungi isn't being nerfed....FOAD to those who say otherwise
				</font>
			</td>

