				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Personally, I'm glad that Fungi wasn't nerfed... of course, I'm speaking as a non-pvp player, and I have one, so I may seem biased.  Honestly, though, I think it's just the bitter, jealous, petty, and generally ugly and wrinkled people who are anti-fungi.  For those who want to be rid of fungus, try some athlete's foot powder.  I didn't get a Fungi Tunic until 49 with my warrior (and no, I wasn't twinked by friends/guildmates/ebay sellers/anything else--I earned it the hard way: in EC.  Ask anyone tunnel rat on Druzzil Ro, and they'll tell ya), so I wouldn't say I'm some PL-crazed n00b.  Yes, I did put one on my monk, along with a CoF and some other toys, and got him to 20 in under 7-1/4 hours.  Does that make me a bastard?  That's up to you to decide.  But don't hate me just because I have better gear than you.  Instead, devote your energy to something productive.  For instance: find a mob.  Target it.  Hit 'A'.  Loot.  Repeat.  Maybe, someday, if you're good, say your prayers each night, and write nice letters to Santa, you'll be able to get one too.<BR>
<BR>
-Llamas Notsheep, 54 Champion of Druzzil Ro, Coven Nex
