			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay I'm sick of whiners everywhere complaining about twinks, a couple things:<BR>
<BR>
1. Any non-pvp server shouldn't have a problem, so their killing stuff faster than you maybe encroaching on your orc hill spawns... they'll be gone in no time.<BR>
<BR>
2. PvP, these people really are kind of rare, and not all of them are that tough. My poorly eqquipped ranger has gotten an orge warrior to about 30% health when he was wearing a fungi tunic, he was about equal level, and I didn't die rather backed off since I was lower. Granted it's a bit of trouble around lvl 6 to maybe 20, (I don't know about other servers but tallon zek pvp starts at lvl 6)but these levels don't really take that long, and the twinks won't always be around, or if they are you can find other places to level.<BR>
<BR>
3. PvP wise fungi tunic isn't so uber alone after level 30 or so, anyone who complains is probably a just a whiner who would complain against a nerf if they ever got a fungi. if you don't think fungi loses some value after 30, take this example, a uber twinked rogue attacked me in the netherbian lair, less than 20 seconds later he's dead my wizard friend nuked him into oblivion easy, fungi tunic had no time to take effect. if you want to nerf stuff why don't you nerf BD gear for ruining casters?<BR>
<BR>
4. I do not now, nor do I expect to anytime soon own a fungi tunic, nor do my friends, so I am in no way biased by a fungi tunic helping me in some way.<BR>
<BR>
Nerfs really are a pain I had a feeling this was a hoax, but the problem is all these people whining about twinks as if it's such a  huge problem. in fact there are far more non-PvP servers than there are PvP servers. And I'm pretty sure they are more populated, so there's no reason VI would nerf something for the minority of pvp servers and piss off all the twinks on blue servers.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
